	  <details class="mb-4 p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
		<summary class="font-medium text-indigo-800 text-lg">Concept Formation.</summary>
		<div class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-md border answer-box-content bg-indigo-100 border-indigo-200">
		  <p>
			Concept formation is the process by which children categorize experiences and objects based on shared features. This ability develops gradually during early childhood.
		  </p>
		  <p>
			Initially, children group items by appearance; later, they use function and category logic. For example, a child might first group all round things together, then learn to classify animals, vehicles, or tools correctly.
		  </p>
		  <p>
			Educational interventions like sorting games, concept mapping, and guided questioning help strengthen this cognitive skill, which is essential for reasoning and learning.
		  </p>
		  <button class="copy-btn mt-4 px-5 py-2 flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 text-white rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2-emerald-500 focus:ring-opacity-50"
