	  <details class="mb-4 p-4 bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
		<summary class="font-medium text-yellow-800 text-lg">High Risk Behaviour in Adolescence.</summary>
		<div class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-md border answer-box-content bg-yellow-100 border-yellow-200">
		  <p>
			Adolescents often engage in high-risk behaviors due to peer pressure, identity exploration, and emotional volatility. Common behaviors include substance use, reckless driving, unsafe sex, and delinquency.
		  </p>
		  <p>
			These actions are partly driven by underdeveloped prefrontal cortex, which affects impulse control. Sensation-seeking and desire for independence also contribute.
		  </p>
		  <p>
			Parents, schools, and communities must collaborate to educate teens about consequences and provide alternatives like sports, arts, or mentorship programs.
		  </p>
		  <button class="copy-btn mt-4 px-5 py-2 flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 text-white rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2-emerald-500 focus:ring-opacity-50"
				  onclick="copyToClipboard(this.previousElementSibling.textContent)">
			<span>Copy Answer</span>
