	<!-- Question Card: Middle Adulthood -->
	<div class="question-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-xl border border-indigo-200">
	  <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-5 flex items-center">
		<span class="mr-2">ðŸ”¹</span> MIDDLE ADULTHOOD
	  </h3>	


	  <details class="mb-4 p-4 bg-pink-50 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
		<summary class="font-medium text-pink-800 text-lg">Describe the cognitive changes during early and middle adulthood.</summary>
		<div class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-md border answer-box-content bg-pink-100 border-pink-200">
		  <p>
			Cognitive development during early and middle adulthood follows a pattern of maturation followed by stabilization and gradual change. These stages represent the prime of cognitive functioning, with some areas peaking and others beginning to plateau.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>Early Adulthood (20â€“40 years):</strong><br>
			This period is marked by cognitive maturity and stability. Key features include:
		  </p>

		  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
			<li><strong>Peak Fluid Intelligence:</strong> Reasoning, problem-solving, and abstract thinking reach their maximum potential</li>
			<li><strong>Strong Working Memory:</strong> Ability to juggle multiple pieces of information simultaneously</li>
			<li><strong>High Processing Speed:</strong> Quick response times and efficient neural communication</li>
			<li><strong>Developed Executive Functions:</strong> Planning, decision-making, and impulse control are well-established</li>
		  </ul>

		  <p>
			<strong>Middle Adulthood (40â€“65 years):</strong><br>
			During this stage, cognitive changes become more apparent, though they are often subtle and vary between individuals.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>1. Processing Speed:</strong><br>
			Neural transmission slows, making it harder to respond quickly to new situations. Driving, multitasking, and fast-paced environments may feel more challenging.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>2. Working Memory:</strong><br>
			Holding and manipulating information in mind becomes more effortful. Remembering phone numbers or following multi-step instructions may require more concentration.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>3. Attention Control:</strong><br>
			Divided attention and selective attention may decline. Staying focused amidst distractions requires conscious effort.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>4. Learning New Skills:</strong><br>
			Learning new concepts or tools (like smartphones or software) takes more time, but mastery is still achievable with repetition and practice.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>5. Emotional Intelligence:</strong><br>
			Emotional regulation improves. Adults become more adept at managing interpersonal conflict, coping with stress, and prioritizing emotionally meaningful experiences.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>6. Expertise and Strategic Thinking:</strong><br>
			Middle-aged adults excel in areas where experience matters â€” medicine, law, teaching, leadership â€” because they rely on established knowledge and strategic thinking.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>7. Metacognition:</strong><br>
			Awareness of one's own thinking patterns increases. Adults become better at identifying what they know, donâ€™t know, and how to learn effectively.
		  </p>

		  <p>
			<strong>Supporting Cognitive Health:</strong><br>
			To maintain cognitive sharpness:
		  </p>

		  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
			<li>Engage in mentally stimulating activities (reading, puzzles, learning)</li>
			<li>Stay physically active to support brain circulation and plasticity</li>
			<li>Maintain social interactions and emotional connections</li>
			<li>Eat a balanced diet rich in antioxidants and omega-3 fatty acids</li>
			<li>Get adequate sleep and manage stress effectively</li>
		  </ul>

		  <p>
			In summary, early and middle adulthood represent a balance of cognitive strengths and emerging challenges. While raw speed and flexibility may decline, wisdom, experience, and emotional intelligence rise â€” supporting overall life competence and decision-making.
		  </p>

		  <button class="copy-btn mt-4 px-5 py-2 flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 text-white rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2-emerald-500 focus:ring-opacity-50"
